---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Exercise Your Muscles — Weekly Workout Plan"
  description="Deep dive: a full 7-day weekly workout plan built on compound barbell push-pull supersets, VO2 max rowing intervals, Zone 2 cardio, and one full recovery day."
  canonicalPath="/exercise-your-muscles/takeaways-workout-plan/"
>
  <a class="overlay-back" href="/exercise-your-muscles/takeaways/">&#8592; Back to Takeaways</a>
  <a class="overlay-close" href="/" aria-label="Close">&times;</a>

  <div class="takeaways-content">
    <span class="takeaways-tag">Exercise Your Muscles</span>
    <h1 class="takeaways-title">Weekly Workout Plan</h1>

    <div class="dd-topic-list">
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#eym-plan-table">7-Day Schedule</a>
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#eym-workout-a">Workout A</a>
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#eym-workout-b">Workout B</a>
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#eym-vo2-rowing">VO2 Max Rowing</a>
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#eym-zone2">Zone 2 Cardio</a>
    </div>

    <div class="tk-section" id="eym-plan-table">
      <div class="tk-section-title">7-Day Schedule</div>
      <div class="fyb-table-wrap">
        <table class="fyb-table" style="min-width:700px">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="width:10%">Day</th>
              <th style="width:18%">Session</th>
              <th style="width:30%">Exercises</th>
              <th style="width:14%">Protocol</th>
              <th style="width:12%">Duration</th>
              <th style="width:16%">Source</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Monday</td>
              <td><strong>Strength A</strong></td>
              <td>
                <ul>
                  <li>Squat</li>
                  <li>Superset: Bench Press ↔ Barbell Row</li>
                </ul>
              </td>
              <td>3 × 6–8 reps</td>
              <td>~30 min</td>
              <td>Sullivan</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Tuesday</td>
              <td><strong>Strength B</strong></td>
              <td>
                <ul>
                  <li>Squat</li>
                  <li>Superset: Overhead Press ↔ Deadlift</li>
                </ul>
              </td>
              <td>3 × 6–8 reps</td>
              <td>~30 min</td>
              <td>Sullivan</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Wednesday</td>
              <td><strong>VO2 Max Rowing</strong></td>
              <td>
                <ul>
                  <li>Rowing machine intervals</li>
                  <li>Max effort sprints with active rest</li>
                </ul>
              </td>
              <td>8 × 1 min on / 2 min off</td>
              <td>~30 min</td>
              <td>Ratey</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Thursday</td>
              <td><strong>Strength A</strong></td>
              <td>
                <ul>
                  <li>Squat</li>
                  <li>Superset: Bench Press ↔ Barbell Row</li>
                </ul>
              </td>
              <td>3 × 6–8 reps</td>
              <td>~30 min</td>
              <td>Sullivan</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Friday</td>
              <td><strong>Strength B</strong></td>
              <td>
                <ul>
                  <li>Squat</li>
                  <li>Superset: Overhead Press ↔ Deadlift</li>
                </ul>
              </td>
              <td>3 × 6–8 reps</td>
              <td>~30 min</td>
              <td>Sullivan</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Saturday</td>
              <td><strong>Zone 2 Cardio</strong></td>
              <td>
                <ul>
                  <li>Bike, row, or incline walk</li>
                  <li>Conversational pace — you can hold a full sentence</li>
                </ul>
              </td>
              <td>130–150 bpm steady state</td>
              <td>30–45 min</td>
              <td>Ratey / Hargrove</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Sunday</td>
              <td><strong>Full Recovery</strong></td>
              <td>
                <ul>
                  <li>No lifting, no cardio</li>
                  <li>Optional: light mobility or walking</li>
                </ul>
              </td>
              <td>—</td>
              <td>Rest</td>
              <td>Sullivan</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tk-section" id="eym-workout-a">
      <div class="tk-section-title">Workout A — Push / Pull Superset</div>
      <p style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:.95rem;color:#5E554B;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem">Performed Monday and Thursday. Three compound barbell movements. The bench press and barbell row are run as a superset — complete one set of bench, rest briefly, then one set of row. Rotate until all 3 sets of each are done. Squats are performed first, straight sets.</p>
      <div class="fyb-table-wrap">
        <table class="fyb-table" style="min-width:580px">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="width:28%">Exercise</th>
              <th style="width:18%">Sets × Reps</th>
              <th style="width:18%">Rest</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Squat</td>
              <td>3 × 6–8</td>
              <td>2–3 min</td>
              <td>Straight sets. Add weight when all 3 sets hit 8 reps.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Bench Press <span style="color:#b79c5c;font-size:0.75rem">↕ Superset</span></td>
              <td>3 × 6–8</td>
              <td>60–90 sec between supersets</td>
              <td>Alternate with Barbell Row. Push until form breaks down.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Barbell Row <span style="color:#b79c5c;font-size:0.75rem">↕ Superset</span></td>
              <td>3 × 6–8</td>
              <td>60–90 sec between supersets</td>
              <td>Pronated grip. Pull to lower chest. Keep back flat.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tk-section" id="eym-workout-b">
      <div class="tk-section-title">Workout B — Push / Pull Superset</div>
      <p style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:.95rem;color:#5E554B;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem">Performed Tuesday and Friday. Three compound barbell movements. The overhead press and deadlift are run as a superset — complete one set of press, rest, then one set of deadlift. Squats are performed first, straight sets.</p>
      <div class="fyb-table-wrap">
        <table class="fyb-table" style="min-width:580px">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="width:28%">Exercise</th>
              <th style="width:18%">Sets × Reps</th>
              <th style="width:18%">Rest</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Squat</td>
              <td>3 × 6–8</td>
              <td>2–3 min</td>
              <td>Straight sets. Same progression — add weight when all 3 × 8.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Overhead Press <span style="color:#b79c5c;font-size:0.75rem">↕ Superset</span></td>
              <td>3 × 6–8</td>
              <td>60–90 sec between supersets</td>
              <td>Strict press. No leg drive. Bar path straight up from shoulders.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Deadlift <span style="color:#b79c5c;font-size:0.75rem">↕ Superset</span></td>
              <td>3 × 6–8</td>
              <td>60–90 sec between supersets</td>
              <td>Conventional pull. Reset on the floor each rep. Back stays neutral.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tk-section" id="eym-vo2-rowing">
      <div class="tk-section-title">VO2 Max Rowing — Wednesday</div>
      <p style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:.95rem;color:#5E554B;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem">Ratey's research shows that high-intensity aerobic exercise produces the largest spike in BDNF and HGH — and rowing hits it without the joint stress of running. The protocol is simple: row at maximum sustainable effort for 1 minute, recover for 2 minutes, repeat 8 times. Total session runs about 30 minutes with warmup and cooldown.</p>
      <div class="fyb-table-wrap">
        <table class="fyb-table" style="min-width:500px">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="width:22%">Phase</th>
              <th style="width:20%">Duration</th>
              <th style="width:20%">Intensity</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Warmup</td>
              <td>5 min</td>
              <td>Easy / Zone 1</td>
              <td>Light rowing to get the blood moving. No effort yet.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Intervals × 8</td>
              <td>1 min on / 2 min off</td>
              <td>Max effort / Easy recovery</td>
              <td>Drive as hard as you can for 60 seconds. Row easy for 2 min. Repeat 8 times.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Cooldown</td>
              <td>5 min</td>
              <td>Easy / Zone 1</td>
              <td>Slow easy rowing to bring heart rate down.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tk-section" id="eym-zone2">
      <div class="tk-section-title">Zone 2 Cardio — Saturday</div>
      <p style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:.95rem;color:#5E554B;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem">Zone 2 builds the aerobic base that makes everything else work better — without generating enough fatigue to interfere with strength gains. The test: you should be able to speak in full sentences the entire time. If you have to pause mid-sentence, slow down. Any low-impact modality works.</p>
      <div class="fyb-table-wrap">
        <table class="fyb-table" style="min-width:500px">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="width:25%">Modality</th>
              <th style="width:20%">Duration</th>
              <th style="width:25%">Target Heart Rate</th>
              <th>Pacing Cue</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Stationary Bike</td>
              <td>30–45 min</td>
              <td>130–150 bpm</td>
              <td>Easy enough to hold a full conversation without pausing.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Rowing Machine</td>
              <td>30–45 min</td>
              <td>130–150 bpm</td>
              <td>Same rule. If breathing gets labored, back off the pace.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="fyb-day">Incline Walk</td>
              <td>30–45 min</td>
              <td>130–150 bpm</td>
              <td>Treadmill at 3–4% grade. No running needed to hit Zone 2.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
</style>
